# This project's style wins

Ignore generic JS/TS internet habits when they conflict with this repo. If a convention is documented here, in `.cursor/rules/`, or in `.cursor/giving_circle.mdx`, follow it. Do not invent alternate "cleaner" patterns.

## Equality

- Never use `==` or `!=`.
- Use `===` and `!==` only.
- Do not use the `!= null` / `== null` idiom. Check null and undefined with strict equality, or structure the code so the type already excludes them.

## Types live with what they describe

- Define types/interfaces in the same module as the value, component, hook, or function they describe.
- Do not create `types.ts` (or similar) dump files for a feature folder.
- Shared types belong only when they are truly shared across modules; put those in an intentional shared location, not a local barrel of leftovers.

## Barrels are public API only

- A folder `index.ts` exports only what outside callers should use.
- Do not re-export internal helpers, private subcomponents, or channel/transport details "just in case".
- If a helper is useful outside the feature, move it to a shared module (`lib/`, shared utilities). Do not leak internals through the barrel.

## Components and files

- Deliver React components in their own files from the start (`export function Name`), not one mega-file to split later.
- Colocate CSS modules as `Name.css.ts` next to the component.
- Keep styling in CSS classes; do not leave static layout styles as inline objects when a classname belongs there.
